               <head>Collection of philosophical works</head>
               
               
               
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79063137  " rend="visible">
                  
                  
                  
                  <summary>A collection of philosophical writings. </summary>
                  
                  
                  
                  <textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="he"/>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79063137">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="1r" to="3v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Tafsir </title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">תפסיר </title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The latter protion of a Judeo-Arabic commentary on the Ten Commandments, ascribed to Eleazar ben Eliezer. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                     
                     
                     
                     <author>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="en">Eleazar ben Eliezer</persName>
                        
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="he">אלעזר בן אליעזר</persName>
                     
                     
                     
                     </author>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="5r" to="6v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḳetsat zaḥul ve-laḥtsan</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">קצת זחול ולחצאן</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Written in a different hand. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
                  
                  
                  
                  <msItem rend="">
                     
                     
                     
                     <locus from="4r" to="47v"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Ḥibur be-astrologiyah uve-filosofiyah</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he">חבור באסטרולוגיה ובפילוסופיה</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>A compilation in an Arabic dialect embodying the teaching of various authorities on astrological. philosophical, and other subjects, the work chiefly relying on Meir ben Isaac Aldabi's Sefer shevile emunah. </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>The scribe broke off near the beginning of folio 5r, the compilation continuing on folio 8r. </p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
                  </msItem>
               
               
               
